Q7ï¸âƒ£ GCD (Greatest Common Divisor)
Program in your notebook
gcd(X, X, X).
gcd(X, Y, D) :-
    X < Y,
    gcd(Y, X, D).
gcd(X, Y, D) :-
    X > Y,
    X1 is X - Y,
    gcd(X1, Y, D).

Explanation

This uses Euclidâ€™s subtraction method:

If both numbers are equal â†’ that number is GCD

If X < Y â†’ swap

If X > Y â†’ subtract smaller from larger

Queries and Outputs
?- gcd(5, 5, D).
D = 5

?- gcd(17, 5, D).
D = 1

?- gcd(51, 17, D).
D = 17


âœ” Correct according to mathematics.
